SetupToolsMcpOnRampText:
Tools, MCP, Skills & Plugins — Safe On-Ramps

/setup only reads local inventory. It never starts MCP servers, installs skills, runs plugins, or executes untrusted commands.

Current inventory:
- MCP: {mcp_result}
- Skills: {skills_result}
- Tools dir: {tools_result}
- Plugins: {plugins_result}
- Hotbar (shared adapters): {hotbar_result}

Paths (redacted home):
- MCP config: {mcp_path}
- Skills: {skills_path}
- Plugins: {plugins_path}

Safe bootstrap (run yourself in a normal terminal or TUI command):
- MCP: /mcp  ·  codewhale mcp init  ·  codewhale doctor
- Skills: /skills  ·  codewhale setup --skills  ·  /skills install <spec>
- Plugins: /plugin  ·  codewhale setup --plugins
- Tools dir: codewhale setup --tools

Side-effectful actions always require explicit confirmation. Plugin commands stay distinct from slash commands; the Hotbar plugin source remains deferred until approval gates land.

See docs/MCP.md and docs/skills/README.md for what still needs manual external setup.
